  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Jeremiah 19:6-9",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jeremiah 19:6-9",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Therefore, behold, the days come — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And are at no great distance; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "that this place shall no more be called Tophet, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — In Joshua’s time it was called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The valley of the son of Hinnom; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "in after ages, it had the name of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Tophet, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "from the noise of drums and tabrets sounding there while children were burning. Here it is foretold that it should have a new name and be called, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The valley of Slaughter. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "See note on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 7:32-33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I will make void the counsel, &c., in this place ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— They shed innocent blood in this place, and in this place God would discomfit them, and cause their blood to be shed by the hands of the Chaldeans. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And I will cause them to eat the flesh of their sons and daughters ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— A terrible judgment threatened by Moses, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 28:53",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and actually fulfilled in the siege of Jerusalem. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Lamentations 4:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
